&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Kennel Attendant with Animal Care Center - Princeton, WV Team&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;isSelectedEnd&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Our Hospital:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;isSelectedEnd&quot;&gt;At Animal Care Center, we believe great veterinary medicine starts with great relationships. Since 1990, our team has been building lasting bonds with pets, clients, and each other across our sister hospitals in Princeton, West Virginia and Pearisburg, Virginia. We&#39;re a community-focused practice where familiar faces, long-tenured team members, and genuine compassion are at the heart of everything we do.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Whether we&#39;re providing preventive care, dentistry, surgery, or helping a worried pet parent through a difficult day, we approach every patient with the same goal: treating them like family. If you&#39;re looking for a hospital where teamwork is valued, relationships matter, and you can make a meaningful impact on pets and the people who love them, we&#39;d love to meet you!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Summary:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Kennel Attendant plays an essential role in maintaining the health, comfort, and safety of hospitalized and boarding pets while supporting the veterinary team in daily hospital operations. This position ensures the hospital environment is clean, organized, and welcoming, and provides compassionate care to all animals during their stay.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Primary Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide daily care for boarded animals, including feeding, watering, walking, bathing, and monitoring behavior and health.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;If applicable, kennel attendants may provide care to hospitalized patients only when directed and supervised by the medical team.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Safely transport animals between kennels, exam rooms, and the lobby, ensuring gentle handling and patient comfort.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist veterinarians and technicians with restraint, positioning, and minor procedures as directed.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Follow detailed feeding, medication, and exercise instructions for boarding pets.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor and report any health or behavioral changes in animals to kennel leadership/medical team promptly.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain cleanliness, disinfection, and organization of all kennels, runs, and facility areas, including outdoor spaces, in accordance with hospital protocols and operating standards.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
